swL2MgmtMIB.name: swL2MgmtMIB
swL2MgmtMIB.description: The Structure of Layer 2 Network Management Information for the proprietary enterprise.

swDevInfoSystemUpTime.name: swDevInfoSystemUpTime
swDevInfoSystemUpTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the switch entered its current operational state. If the current state was entered prior to the last re-initialization, then this object contains a zero value. This value is in the units of seconds.

swDevInfoTotalNumOfPort.name: swDevInfoTotalNumOfPort
swDevInfoTotalNumOfPort.description: The number of ports within this switch. This value is the sum of the ports within this switch.

swDevInfoNumOfPortInUse.name: swDevInfoNumOfPortInUse
swDevInfoNumOfPortInUse.description: The number of ports in this switch connected to the segment or the end stations.

swDevInfoConsoleInUse.name: swDevInfoConsoleInUse
swDevInfoConsoleInUse.description: The usage indication of the console system.

swDevInfoModuleType.name: swDevInfoModuleType
swDevInfoModuleType.description: This object indicates the module type of this port.

swDevInfoFrontPanelLedMode.name: swDevInfoFrontPanelLedMode
swDevInfoFrontPanelLedMode.description: This object indicates the mode of current device front panel LEDs . The front panel LED mode could be changed only by a push button on the device front panel . PortStatusMode : the LEDs respresent ports status. PoEStatusMode : the LEDs respresent POE status.

swDevInfoPowerUnitIndex.name: swDevInfoPowerUnitIndex
swDevInfoPowerUnitIndex.description: Indicates the ID of the unit in the System

swL2DevCtrlStpState.name: swL2DevCtrlStpState
swL2DevCtrlStpState.description: This object can enable or disable the spanning tree algorithm during the runtime of the system.

swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping.name: swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping
swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping.description: This object indicates if the layer 2 Internet Group Management Protocol (IGMP) capture function has been enabled or disabled.

swL2DevCtrlRmonState.name: swL2DevCtrlRmonState
swL2DevCtrlRmonState.description: This object can be enable or disable RMON.

swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter.name: swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter
swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter.description: If the object is set to active, all the statistic counters will be cleared. If set to normal, do nothing.

swL2DevCtrlVlanIdOfFDBTbl.name: swL2DevCtrlVlanIdOfFDBTbl
swL2DevCtrlVlanIdOfFDBTbl.description: Indicates the VLAN ID which the Dot1dTpFdbTable belongs to ; The default value is the DEFAULT_VLAN_ID of the system.

swL2MACNotifyState.name: swL2MACNotifyState
swL2MACNotifyState.description: This object can enable or disable MAC Notification.

swL2MACNotifyHistorySize.name: swL2MACNotifyHistorySize
swL2MACNotifyHistorySize.description: This object indicates the history size of variation MAC in the address table. The default value is 1 .

swL2MACNotifyInterval.name: swL2MACNotifyInterval
swL2MACNotifyInterval.description: This object indicates the time interval in seconds for triggering the MAC notify message.

swL2DevCtrlTelnetState.name: swL2DevCtrlTelnetState
swL2DevCtrlTelnetState.description: This object controls the Telnet status.

swL2DevCtrlTelnetTcpPort.name: swL2DevCtrlTelnetTcpPort
swL2DevCtrlTelnetTcpPort.description: This object can designate a TCP port. When Telnet is disabled this object isn't accessible.

swL2DevAlarmNewRoot.name: swL2DevAlarmNewRoot
swL2DevAlarmNewRoot.description: When the device has become the new root of Spanning Tree, this object decides whether to send a new root trap.

swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange.name: swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange
swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange.description: This object determines whether to send a trap or not when the switch topology has changed. If the object is enabled(3), the topology change trap is sent by the device when any of its configured ports transition from the Learning state to the Forwarding state, or from the Forwarding state to the Blocking state. For the same port transition, the device doesn't send the trap if this object value is set to disabled or other.

swL2DevAlarmLinkChange.name: swL2DevAlarmLinkChange
swL2DevAlarmLinkChange.description: This object determines whether to send a trap or not when the link has changed. If the object is enabled (3), the Link Change trap is sent by the device when any of its port links change. The device doesn't send the trap if this object value is set to disabled or other.

swL2VlanAdvertisementTable.name: swL2VlanAdvertisementTable
swL2VlanAdvertisementTable.description: A table containing the advertisement state for each VLAN configured into the device by (local or network) management.

swL2VlanAdvertisementEntry.name: swL2VlanAdvertisementEntry
swL2VlanAdvertisementEntry.description: Advertisement state for each VLAN configured in the device.

swL2VlanIndex.name: swL2VlanIndex
swL2VlanIndex.description: The VLAN-ID or other identifier referring to this VLAN.

swL2VlanName.name: swL2VlanName
swL2VlanName.description: An administratively assigned string, which may be used to identify the VLAN.

swL2VlanAdvertiseState.name: swL2VlanAdvertiseState
swL2VlanAdvertiseState.description: This object indicates the advertised status of this VLAN entry.

swL2PortInfoTable.name: swL2PortInfoTable
swL2PortInfoTable.description: A table that contains information about every port.

swL2PortInfoEntry.name: swL2PortInfoEntry
swL2PortInfoEntry.description: A list of information for each port of the device.

swL2PortInfoPortIndex.name: swL2PortInfoPortIndex
swL2PortInfoPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module).

swL2PortInfoUnitIndex.name: swL2PortInfoUnitIndex
swL2PortInfoUnitIndex.description: Indicates ID of the unit in the device

swL2PortInfoType.name: swL2PortInfoType
swL2PortInfoType.description: This object indicates the connector type of this port.

swL2PortInfoLinkStatus.name: swL2PortInfoLinkStatus
swL2PortInfoLinkStatus.description: This object indicates the port link status.

swL2PortInfoNwayStatus.name: swL2PortInfoNwayStatus
swL2PortInfoNwayStatus.description: This object indicates the port speed and duplex mode.

swL2PortInfoModuleType.name: swL2PortInfoModuleType
swL2PortInfoModuleType.description: This object indicates the module type of this port.

swL2PortInfoErrorDisabled.name: swL2PortInfoErrorDisabled
swL2PortInfoErrorDisabled.description: This object indicates the blocking type of this port.

swL2PortCtrlTable.name: swL2PortCtrlTable
swL2PortCtrlTable.description: A table that contains control information about every port.

swL2PortCtrlEntry.name: swL2PortCtrlEntry
swL2PortCtrlEntry.description: A list of control information for each port of the device.

swL2PortCtrlPortIndex.name: swL2PortCtrlPortIndex
swL2PortCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortCtrlUnitIndex.name: swL2PortCtrlUnitIndex
swL2PortCtrlUnitIndex.description: Indicates the ID of the unit in the device

swL2PortCtrlAdminState.name: swL2PortCtrlAdminState
swL2PortCtrlAdminState.description: This object decides whether the port is enabled or disabled.

swL2PortCtrlNwayState.name: swL2PortCtrlNwayState
swL2PortCtrlNwayState.description: Choose the port speed, duplex mode, and N-Way function mode.

swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState.name: swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState
swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState.description: The flow control mechanism is different between full duplex mode and half duplex mode. For half duplex mode, the jamming signal is asserted. For full duplex mode, IEEE 802.3x flow control function sends PAUSE frames and receives PAUSE frames.

swL2PortCtrlLockState.name: swL2PortCtrlLockState
swL2PortCtrlLockState.description: This object decides whether the port is locked or not.

swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState.name: swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState
swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState.description: This object decides whether MAC notification is enabled or not.

swL2PortCtrlJumboFrame.name: swL2PortCtrlJumboFrame
swL2PortCtrlJumboFrame.description: This object configure the switch's jumbo frame settings.

swL2PortInformationTable.name: swL2PortInformationTable
swL2PortInformationTable.description: A table that contains information about every port.

swL2PortInformationEntry.name: swL2PortInformationEntry
swL2PortInformationEntry.description: A list of information for each port of the device.

swL2PortInformationPortIndex.name: swL2PortInformationPortIndex
swL2PortInformationPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortInformationMediumType.name: swL2PortInformationMediumType
swL2PortInformationMediumType.description: Indicates medium type of the port number.

swL2PortInformationUnitID.name: swL2PortInformationUnitID
swL2PortInformationUnitID.description: Indicates ID of the unit in the system

swL2PortInformationType.name: swL2PortInformationType
swL2PortInformationType.description: This object indicates the connector type of this port.

swL2PortInformationLinkStatus.name: swL2PortInformationLinkStatus
swL2PortInformationLinkStatus.description: This object indicates the port link status.

swL2PortInformationNwayStatus.name: swL2PortInformationNwayStatus
swL2PortInformationNwayStatus.description: This object indicates the port speed and duplex mode.

swL2PortInformationModuleType.name: swL2PortInformationModuleType
swL2PortInformationModuleType.description: This object indicates the module type of this port.

swL2PortInformationErrorDisabled.name: swL2PortInformationErrorDisabled
swL2PortInformationErrorDisabled.description: This object indicates the blocking type of this port.

swL2PortControlTable.name: swL2PortControlTable
swL2PortControlTable.description: A table that contains control information about every port.

swL2PortControlEntry.name: swL2PortControlEntry
swL2PortControlEntry.description: A list of control information for each port of the device.

swL2PortControlPortIndex.name: swL2PortControlPortIndex
swL2PortControlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortControlMediumType.name: swL2PortControlMediumType
swL2PortControlMediumType.description: Indicates the medium type of the port number.

swL2PortControlUnitIndex.name: swL2PortControlUnitIndex
swL2PortControlUnitIndex.description: Indicates ID of the unit in the device

swL2PortControlAdminState.name: swL2PortControlAdminState
swL2PortControlAdminState.description: This object decides if the port is enabled or disabled.

swL2PortControlNwayState.name: swL2PortControlNwayState
swL2PortControlNwayState.description: Choose the port speed, duplex mode, and N-Way function mode.

swL2PortControlFlowCtrlState.name: swL2PortControlFlowCtrlState
swL2PortControlFlowCtrlState.description: The flow control mechanism is different between full duplex mode and half duplex mode. For half duplex mode, the jamming signal is asserted. For full duplex mode, IEEE 802.3x flow control function sends PAUSE frames and receives PAUSE frames.

swL2PortControlLearningState.name: swL2PortControlLearningState
swL2PortControlLearningState.description: This object decides whether the port is locked or not.

swL2PortControlMACNotifyState.name: swL2PortControlMACNotifyState
swL2PortControlMACNotifyState.description: This object sets each port's MAC notification state.

swL2PortControlMulticastfilter.name: swL2PortControlMulticastfilter
swL2PortControlMulticastfilter.description: This object controls the multicast port filtering mode for a specified port.

swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry.name: swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry
swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2QOSBandwidthControlTable.

swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate.description: Indicates the RX Rate(kbit/sec) of the specifed port. Value 0 means no limit.

swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate.description: Indicates the TX Rate(kbit/sec) of the specifed port. Value 0 means no limit.

swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate.description: The Rx Rate value comes from the RADIUS server, If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrite the locally configured Rx Rate.

swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate.description: The Tx Rate value comes from the RADIUS server, If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrite the locally configured Tx Rate.

swL2QOSSchedulingEntry.name: swL2QOSSchedulingEntry
swL2QOSSchedulingEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2QOSSchedulingTable.

swL2QOSSchedulingMaxPkts.name: swL2QOSSchedulingMaxPkts
swL2QOSSchedulingMaxPkts.description: Indicates the maximum number of packets the hardware priority queue will be allowed to transmit before allowing the next lowest priority queue to transmit its packets. a value between 0 and 255 can be specified.

swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry.name: swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry
swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityTable.

swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass.name: swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass
swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass.description: The number of the switch's hardware priority queue. The switch has four hardware priority queues available. They are numbered between 0 (the lowest priority) and 6 (the highest priority).

swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry.name: swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry
swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityTable.

swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority.name: swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority
swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority.description: The priority value to assign to untagged packets received by the switch ports on the switch.

swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority.name: swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority
swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority.description: Indicates the value of 802.1p comes from RADIUS server. If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrite the local configured value.

swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries.name: swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries
swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries.description: Maximum number of entries in the trunk configuration table (swL2TrunkCtrlTable).

swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries.name: swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries
swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries.description: Current active number of entries in the trunk configuration table.

swL2TrunkCtrlTable.name: swL2TrunkCtrlTable
swL2TrunkCtrlTable.description: This table specifies which ports are grouped as a set of ports(up to 8) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkCtrlEntry.name: swL2TrunkCtrlEntry
swL2TrunkCtrlEntry.description: A list of information specifies which ports are grouped as a set of ports(up to 8) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkIndex.name: swL2TrunkIndex
swL2TrunkIndex.description: The index of logical port trunk. The trunk group number depends on the existence of the unit and module.

swL2TrunkName.name: swL2TrunkName
swL2TrunkName.description: The name of logical port trunk.

swL2TrunkMasterPort.name: swL2TrunkMasterPort
swL2TrunkMasterPort.description: The object indicates the master port number of the port trunk entry. When using Port Trunk, you can not configure the other ports of the group except the master port. Their configuration must be the same as the master port (e.g. speed, duplex, enabled/disabled, flow control, and so on).

swL2TrunkMember.name: swL2TrunkMember
swL2TrunkMember.description: Indicates how many ports are included in this Trunk. The trunk port number depends on the existence of module. The maximum number of ports is 8 for one trunks.

swL2TrunkFloodingPort.name: swL2TrunkFloodingPort
swL2TrunkFloodingPort.description: The object indicates the flooding port number of the port trunk entry. The first port of the trunk is implicitly configured to be the flooding port.

swL2TrunkType.name: swL2TrunkType
swL2TrunkType.description: This object indicates the type of the trunk group. static : is static trunk group lacp : is LACP trunk group .

swL2TrunkState.name: swL2TrunkState
swL2TrunkState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2TrunkAlgorithm.name: swL2TrunkAlgorithm
swL2TrunkAlgorithm.description: This object configures the part of the packet examined by the switch when selecting the egress port for transmitting load-sharing data.

swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort.name: swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort
swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort.description: This object indicates which port will sniff another port to the switch. A trunk port member cannot be configured as a target Snooping port. The port number is the sequential (logical) number which is also applied to bridge MIB, etc.

swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress.name: swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress
swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress.description: This represents the ingress of the source port packet to be sniffed.

swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress.name: swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress
swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress.description: This represents the egress of the source port packet to be sniffed.

swL2MirrorPortState.name: swL2MirrorPortState
swL2MirrorPortState.description: This object indicates the port mirroring state. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different for each of the following values. disabled(2) - writing this value to the object will remove the corresponding entry from the table. enabled(3) - this entry will reside in the table.

swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans.name: swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans
swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans.description: Maximum number of VLANs in the layer 2 IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable).

swL2IGMPCtrlTable.name: swL2IGMPCtrlTable
swL2IGMPCtrlTable.description: This table controls the VLAN's IGMP function. Its scale depends on the current VLAN state (swL2VlanInfoStatus). If VLAN is in disabled mode, there is only one entry in the table, with index 1. If VLAN is in Port-Base or 802.1q mode, the number of entries can be up to 12, with an index range from 1 to 12.

swL2IGMPCtrlEntry.name: swL2IGMPCtrlEntry
swL2IGMPCtrlEntry.description: The entry in IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable). The entry is effective only when IGMP capture switch (swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping) is enabled.

swL2IGMPCtrlVid.name: swL2IGMPCtrlVid
swL2IGMPCtrlVid.description: This object indicates the IGMP control entry's VLAN ID. If VLAN is disabled, the VID is always 0 and cannot be changed by management users. If VLAN is in Port-Base mode, the VID is arranged from 1 to 12, fixed form. If VLAN is in 802.1q mode, the VID setting can vary from 1 to 4094 by management user, and the Vid in each entry must be unique in the IGMP Control Table.

swL2IGMPQueryInterval.name: swL2IGMPQueryInterval
swL2IGMPQueryInterval.description: The frequency at which the IGMP Host-Query packets are transmitted on this switch.

swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime.name: swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime
swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime.description: The maximum query response time on this switch.

swL2IGMPRobustness.name: swL2IGMPRobustness
swL2IGMPRobustness.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet. If a subnet is expected to have a high loss, the Robustness Variable may be increased. IGMP is robust to (Robustness Variable-1) packet losses.

swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval.name: swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval
swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval.description: The Last Member Query Interval is the Max Response Time inserted into Group-Specific Queries sent in response to Leave Group messages, and is also the amount of time between Group-Specific Query messages.

swL2IGMPHostTimeout.name: swL2IGMPHostTimeout
swL2IGMPHostTimeout.description: The timer value for sending IGMP query packet when none was sent by the host in the LAN. The timer works in per-VLAN basis. Our device will be activated to send the query message if the timer has expired. Please reference RFC2236-1997.

swL2IGMPRouteTimeout.name: swL2IGMPRouteTimeout
swL2IGMPRouteTimeout.description: The Router Timeout is how long a host must wait after hearing a Query before it may send any IGMPv2 messages.

swL2IGMPLeaveTimer.name: swL2IGMPLeaveTimer
swL2IGMPLeaveTimer.description: When a query receives a Leave Group message for a group that has group members on the reception interface, it sends Group-Specific Queries every swL2IGMPLeaveTimer to the group being left.

swL2IGMPQueryState.name: swL2IGMPQueryState
swL2IGMPQueryState.description: This object decides if the IGMP query is enabled or disabled.

swL2IGMPCurrentState.name: swL2IGMPCurrentState
swL2IGMPCurrentState.description: This object indicates the current IGMP query state.

swL2IGMPCtrlState.name: swL2IGMPCtrlState
swL2IGMPCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different for each of the following values. disable(2) - IGMP funtion is disabled for this entry. enable(3) - IGMP funtion is enabled for this entry.

swL2IGMPFastLeaveState.name: swL2IGMPFastLeaveState
swL2IGMPFastLeaveState.description: This object indicates the fast_leave status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disable(2) - IGMP fast-leave funtion is disabled for this entry. enable(3) - IGMP fast-leave funtion is enabled for this entry.

swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable.name: swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable
swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable.description: The table contains the current number of IGMP query packets which have been captured by this device, as well as the IGMP query packets sent by the device.

swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry.name: swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry
swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry.description: Information about current IGMP query information, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrState of associated VLAN entires are all enabled.

swL2IGMPInfoVid.name: swL2IGMPInfoVid
swL2IGMPInfoVid.description: This object indicates the VID of the associated IGMP info table entry. It follows swL2IGMPCtrlVid in the associated entry of the IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable).

swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount.name: swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount
swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount.description: This object indicates the number of query packets received since the IGMP function has been enabled, on a per-VLAN basis.

swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount.name: swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount
swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount.description: This object indicates the send count of IGMP query messages, on a per-VLAN basis. In case of the IGMP timer expiration, the switch sends IGMP query packets to related VLAN member ports and increments this object by 1.

swL2IGMPInfoTable.name: swL2IGMPInfoTable
swL2IGMPInfoTable.description: The table containing current IGMP information which have been captured by this device, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entries are all enabled. Note that the priority of IGMP table entries is lower than the Filtering Table, i.e. if there is a table hash collision between the entries of the IGMP Table and the Filtering Table inside the switch H/W address table, the Filtering Table entry will overwrite the colliding entry of the IGMP Table. See swL2FilterMgmt description also.

swL2IGMPInfoEntry.name: swL2IGMPInfoEntry
swL2IGMPInfoEntry.description: Information about current IGMP information which was captured by this device, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entries are all enabled.

swL2IGMPVid.name: swL2IGMPVid
swL2IGMPVid.description: This object indicates the VID of individual IGMP table entries. It shows the VID of IGMP report information captured on the network.

swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr.name: swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr
swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr.description: This object identifies group ip address which have been captured from the IGMP packet, on a per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPMacAddr.name: swL2IGMPMacAddr
swL2IGMPMacAddr.description: This object identifies mac addresses which correspond to swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr, on a per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPPortMap.name: swL2IGMPPortMap
swL2IGMPPortMap.description: This object indicates which ports belong to the same multicast group, on a per-Vlan basis. Each multicast group has a octect string to indicate with port map. The most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'(Note that the setting of the bit corresponding to the port from which a frame is received is irrelevant). The 4 octets represent one unit port according to its logic port. If the unit has less then 32 port, the other ports don't care and just fill in zero.

swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount.name: swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount
swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount.description: This object indicates how many report packets were received by the device corresponding with this entry where the IGMP function is enabled, on a per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTable.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTable
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTable.description: The information of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN table.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanid.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanid
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanid.description: This object indicates the VLAN id of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN entry.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanName.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanName
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanName.description: This object indicates the VLAN name of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN entry.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanSourcePort.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanSourcePort
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanSourcePort.description: This object indicates the portlist of the source ports of IGMP snooping multicast VLAN. The source ports will be set as tag ports of the VLAN entry and the IGMP control messages received from the member ports would be forwarded to the source ports.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanMemberPort.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanMemberPort
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanMemberPort.description: This object indicates the portlist of the member ports of IGMP snooping multicast VLAN. The source ports will be set to untag ports of the vlan entry and the IGMP control messages received from the member ports would be forwarded to the source ports.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRowStatus.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRowStatus
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortTable.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortTable
swL2IGMPRouterPortTable.description: The information of the router port table.

swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanid.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanid
swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanid.description: This object indicates the VLAN id of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanName.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanName
swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanName.description: This object indicates the VLAN name of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortStaticPortList.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortStaticPortList
swL2IGMPRouterPortStaticPortList.description: This object indicates the static portlist of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortDynamicPortList.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortDynamicPortList
swL2IGMPRouterPortDynamicPortList.description: This object indicates the dynamic portlist of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortForbiddenPortList.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortForbiddenPortList
swL2IGMPRouterPortForbiddenPortList.description: This object indicates the forbidden portlist of the router port entry.

swL2TrafficSegTable.name: swL2TrafficSegTable
swL2TrafficSegTable.description: This table specifies that the port can just forward traffic to the specific port list.

swL2TrafficSegEntry.name: swL2TrafficSegEntry
swL2TrafficSegEntry.description: A list of information specifying the port with its traffic forward list.

swL2TrafficSegPort.name: swL2TrafficSegPort
swL2TrafficSegPort.description: The port number of the logical port.

swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts.name: swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts
swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts.description: The port list that the specific port can forward traffic to.

swL2BroadcastSegFilterPorts.name: swL2BroadcastSegFilterPorts
swL2BroadcastSegFilterPorts.description: The port list that the specific port can filter broadcast packets from.

swL2PortSecurityControlTable.name: swL2PortSecurityControlTable
swL2PortSecurityControlTable.description: The port security feature controls the address learning capability and the traffic forwarding decision. Each port can have this function enabled or disabled. When it is enabled and a number is given said N, which allows N addresses to be learned at this port, the first N learned addresses are locked at this port as a static entry. When the learned addresses number reaches N, any incoming packet that has not learned a source address is discarded (e.g. dropped) and no more new addresses can be learned on this port.

swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr.name: swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr
swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr.description: Indicates allowable number of addresses to be learned at this port.

swL2PortSecurityMode.name: swL2PortSecurityMode
swL2PortSecurityMode.description: Indicates the mode of locking address. In deleteOnTimeout (3) mode, the locked addresses can be aged out after the aging timer has expired. In this mode, when the locked address has aged out, the number of addresses that can be learned has to increase by one. In deleteOnReset (4) mode, the locked addresses are not aged out unless the system is restarted. This is to prevent port movement or intrusion.
